## Setup: this is where we use Perl and PG objects (Required)

Context("Numeric");
$seed = random(1, 1000, 1);
# warn("seed: " . $seed);

rserve_eval("set.seed($seed)");
## do not need to download data
@data = rserve_eval('
sigma <- round(runif(1, min=0.2, max=0.9), 1)
beta1 <- round(runif(1, min=-0.9, max=-0.5), 1)
beta2 <- round(runif(1, min=-0.6, max=-0.1), 1)
beta3 <- round(runif(1, min=0.1, max=0.4), 1)

# part (a)
ans.a <- sigma^2 * (1 + beta1^2 + beta2^2 + beta3^2)
ans.b <- sigma^2 * (beta1 + beta1 * beta2 + beta2 * beta3)
ans.c <- sigma^2 * (beta2 + beta1 * beta3) / ans.a

ans.a <- round(ans.a, 4)
ans.b <- round(ans.b, 4)
ans.c <- round(ans.c, 4)
c(ans.a, ans.b, ans.c, sigma, beta1, beta2, beta3)
');

$sigma = $data[3];
$beta1 = $data[4];
$beta2 = $data[5];
$beta3 = $data[6];

#########################################################
## Main Text: where all text goes (Required)
Context()->texStrings;

BEGIN_TEXT

Let \(Z (t)\) denote a white noise process with mean zero and variance \($sigma ^2 \). Define the stochastic process \(X (t)\) by

\[ X(t) = Z(t) + $beta1 Z(t-1) + $beta2 Z(t-2) + $beta3 Z(t-3)
\]
Provide the following, each to two decimal places.

$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (a)  $EBOLD
\( Var(X(t)) \)
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (b) $EBOLD
\( Cov(X(t), X(t+1))\)
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR
$BBOLD Part (c) $EBOLD
The autocorrelation function of \(X(t)\) at lag 2.
\{ans_rule(7)\}
$BR
$BR

END_TEXT

#########################################################
## Answers evaluation (Required)
ANS( num_cmp($data[0], tol=> 0.02) );
ANS( num_cmp($data[1], tol=> 0.02) );
ANS( num_cmp($data[2], tol=> 0.02) );

#########################################################
## Solution (Optional but recommended)
Context()->texStrings;

BEGIN_SOLUTION
$BBOLD Part (a) $EBOLD
We have 
$BR
\[ 
Var(X(t) ) = $sigma ^2 * (1 + {($beta1)}^2 + {($beta2)}^2 + {($beta3)}^2) = $data[0].
\]

$BBOLD Part (b) $EBOLD
The value is found via
$BR
\[ 
\begin{eqnarray*}
Cov(X(t), X(t+1)) &=& Cov(Z(t) + $beta1 Z(t-1) + $beta2 Z(t-2) + $beta3 Z(t-3),  \\
 && Z(t+1) + $beta1 Z(t) + $beta2 Z(t-1) + $beta3 Z(t-2) )\\
&=& $sigma^2 * ($beta1 + {($beta1 * $beta2)} + {($beta2 * $beta3)} = $data[1].
\end{eqnarray*}
\]

$BBOLD Part (c) $EBOLD
To find the acf at lag 2, we first require \(Cov(X (t), X (t + 2)) \) :
$BR
\[ 
\begin{eqnarray*}
Cov(X(t), X(t+2)) &=& Cov(Z(t) + $beta1 Z(t-1) + $beta2 Z(t-2) + $beta3 Z(t-3), \\
&& Z(t+2) + $beta1 Z(t+1) + $beta2 Z(t) + $beta3 Z(t-1)) \\
&=& $sigma^2  * ($beta2 + {($beta1 * $beta3)}).
\end{eqnarray*}
\]
The acf at lag 2 is therefore
\[ 
\begin{eqnarray*}
\frac{Cov(X(t), X(t+2))}{Var(X(t)))} = $data[2].
\end{eqnarray*}
\]

END_SOLUTION

